Bandits have again attacked commuters at Birnin-Gwari Local Government Area of Kaduna State. The assailants laid siege at Zankoro, along dreaded Birnin-Gwari-Kaduna Highway on Sunday. PRNigeria reports that they killed nine people, including 3 infants. The victims were on their way to a ceremony at Doka, Birnin-Gwari Local Government. Similarly, bandits, on Monday morning at the same Zankoro, shot sporadically and abducted an unspecified number of people. Six people wounded are receiving treatment at Buruku along Kaduna-Birnin-Gwari Highway.